Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:24.01,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\1c&H000000&\blur1\fscx99\fscy125\bord0\shad0\pos(332,73)}Innoshima Hiking Path
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:24.01,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fs32.5\1c&H000000&\fscx100\fscy90\bord0\blur1\shad0\pos(248,145)}HONINBOU
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:24.01,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fs33.5\1c&H000000&\fscx100\fscy90\bord0\blur1\shad0\pos(419,145)}SHUUSAKU
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:24.01,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\an4\fs13.5\1c&H000000&\fscx100\fscy140\bord0\blur1\shad0\pos(107,287)}He was born in Gaikaichou of Innoshima in 1829 under the name Torajirou.\NBorn with a passion for Go, just like his mother. he became the top player\Nin the area by the time he was six. In 1841 he changed his name to Shuusaku,\Nrose by one dan in strength every year, and became 4-dan by the time he\Nwas 15. When Shuusaku became 20, he was decided to become the succesor\Nof the Honinbou family, and received the 6-dan title and married Honinbou\NJouwa's daughter Tachibana. In 1848 he entered the castle to play go, and\Nmade a never before seen record of 19 straight wins. But he died at the age\Nof 34 in the year 1862 when there was a Cholera epidemic in Edo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:24.01,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fs18\1c&H000000&\blur1\fscx100\fscy75\bord0\shad0\pos(476,406)}Hiroshima\NPrefecture
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.26,0:12:21.04,Background,,0,0,0,,Yup, yup. It's the remains of the\Nhouse Shuusaku was born in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.22,0:12:23.60,Background,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the kind of place you wanted to go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.01,0:12:33.97,bannersign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1.2\fscx101\fscy110\an4\fs26\frz271.8\move(316,114,316,-425,16,9943)\c&H9B66DA&}THE TOP {\fscx116}GO GO{\fsp2}D OF
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.01,0:12:34.02,bannersign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1.2\fscy110\an4\fs26\frz271.8\fscx125\fsp2\move(328,482,327.84,-60,0,0)\c&H9B66DA&}JAPAN
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.01,0:12:34.02,bannersign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1.2\fscx131\fscy90\fs32\an4\frz270\move(236,459,236,-81,16,9993)\c&H60504A&}HONINBOU SHUUSAKU
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:27.02,Thinking,,0,0,0,,A Memorial Museum...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.52,0:12:30.02,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Would Sai go to a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:34.02,Thinking,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling that he wouldn't\Nbe very comfortable there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you as excited as I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:41.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Sai! Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.91,0:12:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They said the memorial museum\Nis towards the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:45.29,NoteArial,,0,0,0,,{\fs17.5\blur0.8\c&H6F6559&\4c&HFFFFFF&\fscx100\fscy190\bord0\shad1.5\pos(416,-19)}GRAVE\N\NOF THE\N\NHONINBOU
